items.name: Minecraft Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about the Minecraft Wikia!
items.desc: Learn more about Minecraft! Minecraft is a sandbox construction game that allows players to build and destroy different types of blocks in a 3D environment. Players roam free, to do and build anything they want!

items.name: Minecraft Constuctions Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Constuctions Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Constructions Wikia
items.desc: The Minecraft Constructions wiki is a wiki where you can share and find blueprints for everything you could want to build in Minecraft, from cannons and houses to redstone circuits and traps. This wiki now requires that all articles follow the correct form and guidelines, which you can read about below. If you have no idea what minecraft is, what blocks are, or the details, go to Minecraft Wikipedia and learn about it!click here to download mincraft.

items.name: Minecraft Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Wiki
items.headline: Bauweltspiel Minecraft
items.desc: Dieses Wiki handelt von dem Sandboxgame Minecraft. Man findet hier die Informationen zu diesem Spiel. Alle wichtigen Informationen, wie Bauanleitungen, Bedeutungen, Fundorte, Verwendung und Herstellung verschiedenster Dinge in Minecraft sind hier aufzufinden. Auch kann man sich hier einige Tipps und Tricks zu einzelnen Dingen holen.

items.name: Minecraft Fanon Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Minecraft Fanon wiki
items.desc: The Minecraft Fanon wiki is a great, user friendly place to put all of your ideas for Minecraft! We have two welcoming friendly admins and are looking for a third. We have close to 100 pages, and the wiki is very neat and organized. As for content, we have mobs, items, blocks, characters and people, fanfictions, and so much more! So come join the wiki today, it`s a really fun place, and you could make it even better!

items.name: Minecraft Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Wiki
items.headline: Maailman suosituin suomenkielinen Minecraft Wiki
items.desc:
Minecraft on hankala peli, varsinkin aloittelijoille. Ei hätää!

Minecraft Wikistä löydät jokaisesta esineestä, kuutiosta, joukosta tai itse pelistä kaiken tarvitsemasi tiedon. Wikissä on jo yli 400 sivua ja luku kasvaa jatkuvasti.

Wikin 8 byrokraattia, ylläpitäjät, moderaattorit ja aktiiviset käyttäjät pitävät huolen, että wiki on koko ajan ajan tasalla.
Haluatko olla yksi heistä? Tarvitset vain käyttäjän ja olet valmis muokkaamaan. Kehittyneen käyttäjäastejärjestelmämme ansiosta pelkällä aktiivisuudella voi päästä byrokraatiksi.

Mikäli tarvitset välitöntä apua, lähetä viestiä byrokraateille, jotka auttavat mielellään sinua, tai mene chattiin.

Jos siis tarvitset apua pelin toiminnassa tai vaikkapa craftausresepteissä, tule Minecraft wikiin!

items.title: Minecraft buildcraft Wiki
items.headline: Minecraft Buildcraft Wiki
items.desc: Buildcraft Minecraft Wiki is dedicated to the buildcraft feature in the popular Minecraft game. Buildcraft is a full featured modification ("mod") for Minecraft that adds automated building, mining and crafting as well as pipe transport and item sorting to the Minecraft experience.

items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraftdesign Wiki
items.desc:
Stuck for ideas in your Minecraft world? Well look no further! This working progress site will combine all of the designs, ideas and functions you need to fill your Minecraft world from sky to bedrock!

We pride on our community and we are in the process of exchanging everything to our Forum and making it our main site, hop on over and register!

items.name: Minecraft-archaeology Wiki
items.title: Minecraft-archaeology Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Archaeology Wiki
items.desc: The Minecraft Archaeology Wiki is a Wiki about the fan made Archeology mod for Minecraft. This mod adds fossil blocks, scarab tools and eventually dinosaurs to the game. This wiki helps to explain how the fossil blocks work and what the percentage chance for various drops and dinosaurs are. Please feel free to contribute!

items.name: Minecraft Technic Pack Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Technic Pack Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Technic Pack Wikia!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Technic Pack Wikia, which is your source for all things related to Technic Pack. The Technic Pack is a mod pack for the popular game Minecraft. It adds great features such as BuildCraft, Industrial Craft², Equivilant Exchange, Mo' Creatures plus many more. 

We are growing our wikia right now so feel free to add things we don't have or update things we do! If you want to see something added please say so on our suggestions page.

items.name: Paulsoaresjr Wiki
items.title: Paulsoaresjr Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about the Paul Sores, Jr. Wikia
items.desc: Paulsoaresjr is the first person on YouTube to make Minecraft Tutorials. He is also a husband, father and business man. This is his wikia about his Minecraft adventures and tutorials. He also does things such as DayZ, Indie Game test drives and more, he has worked hard to bring us entertainment, Thumbs Up To Paul! Paul loves adventure and is very impulsive. Please remember that this Wiki is a work in progress.

items.headline: The Minecraft Pocket Edition Wiki - The Perfect MCPE Fan Site
items.desc: The Minecraft Pocket Edition Wiki is a community of dedicated fans that work together to create one of the most complete databases on the game, Minecraft Pocket Edition.

items.name: Minecraftmodcustomstuff Wiki
items.title: Minecraftmodcustomstuff Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft wiki!
items.desc: Custom Stuff is a Minecraft mod developed by CubeX2 that allows for the addition of blocks and items into the game without having to code java. By using a basic mockup you can add a variety of common things to the game including blocks, ores, tools, and so-forth. With a little knowledge of javascript you can also create many more impressive things such as crops and even trees! If you've ever wanted to create a Minecraft mod but didn't want to learn java to do it, this mod is for you!

items.name: ScottLand Minecraft Wiki
items.title: ScottLand Minecraft Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the ScottLand Minecraft Wiki
items.desc: This is the official wiki for Zack Scott's Scottland Minecraft server.    You will find a bunch of great stuff on the Scottland Minecraft server Wiki such as funny jokes, animated GIFS, comical pictures and much more! You can also catch up on the latest posts by Zack Scott himself, and all of the Scottland players. You can also watch the Let's Plays that Zack Scott and the other server members do here.

items.name: Minecraft Players Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Players Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Players wiki!
items.desc:
This wiki is about you. 
Share on how you got started out.
Share your amazing encounters you have.
Create a page on your player, and give your player a background. 
Create a story out of it.
Make a complete story about yourself, a fictional place, or what happened on your first day in Minecraft!

Minecraft Creativity at it's finest.

items.name: Minecraft Fanfictions Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Fanfictions Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Minecraft Fanfictions Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to Minecraft Fanfictions Wiki! It's a wonderful community where you can contribute your minecraft fan-made stories, mobs, dimensions, and more! It is also very viewer friendly so that children of most ages can view as well. While you create things, you also earn achievements for your great accomplishments. Hope to see you on!

items.desc: Minecraft is a game that leaves open endless possibilities for the player, and when players are given such freedom thier creativity comes alive. The goal of the Minecraft Creations Wiki is to provide a place where Minecraft players can come together and share the imaginative and purely amazing creations they have made. Become a member of our awesome community and share your creation today!

items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft: Xbox 360/Playstation Edition Wiki
items.desc: The goal of this wiki is to provide a place where all information about Minecraft: Xbox 360/Playstation Edition can come together and be shared freely with everyone. Become a member of our community and help us expand! If you want to add information about things like games modes that you or others have invented on Minecraft, then please add it to the Minecraft: Xbox 360 Edition Fanon Wiki. Happy editing!

items.name: Minecraft Wiki
items.title: Minecraft Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Minecraft Wiki!
items.desc: This wiki is about the very popular first person sandbox game created by a company known as Mojang. Mojang was founded in May 2009 by a man named Markus Persson (or Notch), Jakob Porsér, and Carl Manneh. Notch owns Mojang. Within a year, Mojang grew to a size of 12 employees. Some people under-rate Minecraft for things such as "bad graphics", but in the end, they are missing out on an extremely fun game.
